    "revelation": "The tidal pulse and the drift operate at different speeds. This is how weather systems work — a slow ground-level pressure and a fast atmospheric flutter, both moving in the same body of air.",
    "diagnosis": "Migration Path is the first preset to combine tidalDepth with FM. At tidalRate=0.3 Hz the tidal sweep has a period of ~3 seconds — slow enough to feel like breath. The FM satellite rides on top of the tide, drifting at 0.08 Hz. Two modulations, two personalities."
